description: My research interests include anticancer peptide prediction, peptide bioinformatics, and machine learningbased modeling using physicochemical and evolutionary features. I aim to develop interpretable and robust computational frameworks that perform reliably under limited data scenarios.
Omni is a modular data ingestion and extraction framework built with DDD and Clean Architecture, designed for scalable analytics, machine learning, and external data integration.
A Hybrid Machine Learning Framework for Accurate Sales Demanding Forecasting

An AI-powered ETL testing framework that combines rule-based validation, statistical analysis, machine learning, and advanced AI techniques to help teams catch data quality issues early, surface potential regulatory risks (AML, structuring, sanctions patterns), and produce actionable reports for engineers, analysts, and compliance reviewers.
Machine Learning framework for the MNIST dataset, built in Rust
Machine Learning Framework for Formula 1 Race Strategy Optimization
A comprehensive platform for automated evaluation of AI agent responses using multi-metric analysis, built with React TypeScript frontend and Python backend with machine learning capabilities.

A .NET Core application for house price prediction using machine learning.  Built with ASP.NET Core, Entity Framework Core, and ML.NET.  Features RESTful API, data validation, and comprehensive testing.
A machine learning framework for predicting hydrolytic degradation kinetics of biodegradable polyesters (PLA, PLGA, PCL, PGA) for biomedical implant applications.

This autonomous traffic orchestration framework leverages computer vision and machine learning to dynamically calibrate signal phases via real-time spatiotemporal analytics. By superseding static temporal regimes, it mitigates congestion, optimizes throughput, and facilitates preemptive routing for emergency responders.

The proposed research study will develop a comprehensive end-to-end Ma- chine Learning (ML) system to mitigate analytical challenges posed by BRFSS data and ensure the overall rigor and repro- ducibility of the ML-based approach.
A machine learning framework for detecting phishing attacks across Email, SMS, and malicious URLs using a unified Random Forest classifier and signal-preserving NLP.
Googles open-source machine learning framework, widely used for AI projects.
multiple machine learning and deep learning practice projects and framework practice repo
In Silico Prediction of Shelf-Life for Marinated Meat Products Using an Integrative Framework of Machine Learning and Text Mining
An extensible framework for reproducible machine learning experiments
HLSFactory: A Framework Empowering High-Level Synthesis Datasets for Machine Learning and Beyond

CircumSpectrum is a flux-based framework that converts bulk and single-cell RNA-seq data into metabolic fingerprints using genome-scale models and machine learning. It includes RADAR, SOURIS, and CORALIE modules for reaction-level, cross-cohort, and multi-tier correlation analyses.
MULTI-evolve: a machine learning-guided end-to-end framework for engineering hyperactive multi-mutant proteins

Experimental framework and Bayesian machine learning pipeline for estimating soil Volumetric Water Content (VWC) using passive UHF RFID technology. Includes physics-informed preprocessing, statistical modeling (Bayesian regression), and sensor data analysis for indirect sensing in smart agriculture and IoUT contexts.

RECLAIM (Reservoir Estimation of Capacity Loss using AI-based Methods) is a globally scalable machine learning framework to predict absolute sedimentation rates using observed records and multi-decadal Earth observations from satellite data.
The R code for A scalable Bayesian double machine learning framework for high dimensional causal estimation, with application to racial disproportionality assessment
A minimal example of how to share a common wgpu device between the Bevy game engine and the Burn machine learning framework

This repository contains a collection of Python programs and Jupyter notebooks focusing on Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Machine Learning (ML) algorithms. It covers implementations, experiments, and hands-on code examples using popular libraries and frameworks in Python.

AI Driven Semantic Framework for Advanced Cyber Threat Analysis and Sharing using comprehensive machine learning and deep learning framework for real-time cyber threat detection, analysis, and intelligence sharing.
Impact-induced failure mode prediction of RC beams and columns using a machine learning framework with improved data-algorithm strategies
Atlantic: Automated Data Preprocessing Framework for Machine Learning

This project focuses on customer behavior analysis using the RFMT framework combined with machine learning techniques. It segments customers into meaningful groups to help organizations optimize marketing strategies and enhance customer relationships.
Real-time Federated Data Platform Harnessing Machine Learning for Adaptive Intelligent Workflow Optimization Framework
a small machine learning framework implemented from scratch
AI-based Weather Forecasting System using Machine Learning (Random Forest) and Django web framework with real-time data integration.
This is the official repository for CardioLab. A machine and deep learning framework for the estimation and monitoring of laboratory abnormalities throught ECG data.
Development of an Explainable Machine Learning Framework for Intelligent Train Operation

This study introduces a Machine Learning (ML)-assisted framework using X-ray Diffraction (XRD) data to predict the properties of antimicrobial nanoparticles. The Random Forest Regressor predicts crystallite size with 1.84 nm MAE, and the Random Forest Classifier identifies material phase with 99% accuracy.
A machine learning framework for urban wellness prediction using adaptive domain-aware random forests to achieve cross-city performance optimization across six major Chinese cities.
Multi-label classifiers and evaluation procedures using the Weka machine learning framework.

This project demonstrates a complete machine learning pipeline, from model development to deployment, emphasizing practical usability and clear visualization. It serves as a reference for applying machine learning techniques to tabular healthcare data and for deploying models using lightweight web frameworks such as Streamlit.
A Spatio-Temporal Explainable Machine Learning Framework for Crime Hotspot Prediction
A curated list of tools, frameworks, platforms, and resources for Machine Learning Operations (MLOps).
DeepMech: A Machine Learning Framework for Chemical Reaction Mechanism Prediction

clinical machine learning framework designed to predict patient-specific response to riluzole therapy in Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis (ALS) using longitudinal respiratory and motor function data from the PRO-ACT dataset.
The Sentinel Framework builds on this progress by adding biometric authentication and machine learning to captive portals, aiming to provide secure and password-free network access.
Badr is a framework for training fair machine-learning models that minimize a chosen fairness metric while preserving Pareto-optimal performance across sensitive groups.
End to End Machine learning projects of Finance analytics in CRISP DM Framework
A Dual-Pipeline Machine Learning Framework for Automated Sleep Disorder Screening using Hybrid Resampling and Ensemble Learning.
This project develops a predictive framework for credit risk under IFRS 9 standards. It leverages a dataset of over 32,500 entries to predict the Probability of Default (PD).
Machine learning framework for strain-level prediction
A reproducible, simulator-driven reference implementation for customer churn prediction pipelines using web analytics and machine learning.
This framework extends DEA by training ensemble machine learning models to predict DEA efficiency scores, enabling scalable, forward-looking efficiency analysis.

This repository explores Machine Learning through projects, scripts, and tutorials. It covers data preprocessing, model training, evaluation, and deployment using frameworks like scikit-learn, TensorFlow, and PyTorch, with applications in classification, regression, NLP, and computer vision.

This repository implements an institutional-grade asset pricing framework based on the Gu, Kelly, and Xiu (2020) methodology, leveraging machine learning to capture non-linearities in equity risk premia.
This repository presents AuDaCE (Audio Dataset Controlled Environment), a framework aiming at simplifying the management of machine learning datasets based on audio.

A framework to evaluate Large Language Model (LLM) predictions, explanations, and counterfactuals against traditional Machine Learning models using clustering-based Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG), baseline methods, and automated evaluation pipelines.
Machine learning evaluation frameworks
An Open Source Machine Learning Framework for Everyone

A hybrid data quality framework integrating Pandera schema validation and unsupervised ML (Isolation Forest, DBSCAN and Local Outlier Factor) to secure traffic collision data. This modular pipeline automates geospatial and logical anomaly detection with 88.5% precision, delivering explainable reports via an interactive Streamlit dashboard.

A unified machine learning framework for dyslexia detection using eye-tracking data from both children and adults. The repository benchmarks supervised and unsupervised models to evaluate cross-age and cross-dataset generalization.
Reinforcement-Machine learningbased optimization framework autonomously generates intermediate video frames by modeling latent motion trajectories.
Explainable AI (XAI) framework designed to provide transparent, interpretable insights for both tabular and image-based machine learning models.

This Python package  provides a robust framework to automatically train, evaluate, and visualize multiple machine learning models for both Classification and Regression problems.  It includes features for automatic best model recommendation, colorful confusion matrices, and comprehensive performance plots.
a superresolution framework for CT images based on machine learning

Physics-informed and explainable ML framework for predicting and optimizing hardness in high-entropy alloys. Integrates descriptor engineering, supervised learning, SHAP-based interpretability, physics validation, and statistical optimization for robust, interpretable HEA design.

An acausal modeling framework for automatically parallelized scientific machine learning (SciML) in Julia. A computer algebra system for integrated symbolics for physics-informed machine learning and automated transformations of differential equations
Predict football match outcomes using the W-5 Multi-Agent AI Consensus Framework, achieving high accuracy with a blend of AI and machine learning techniques.
probably approximately correct (PAC) learning is a framework for mathematical analysis of machine learning

This repository provides a comprehensive framework for enhancing nuclear Density Functional Theory (DRHBc) predictions through physics-informed machine learning. Our approach combines -learning with domain-specific feature engineering to significantly improve the accuracy of nuclear binding energies, charge radii, and separation energy predictions

A machine learning framework designed to classify the habitability potential of exoplanets using planetary and stellar parameters. This project implements various classification models to analyze Kepler Space Telescope data and identify Earth-like candidates.
Machine Learning and Deep Learning based projects developed using Python and python related frameworks

A multifaceted framework for analysing, modeling, and managing credit risk, combining data engineering, statistical modeling, decision logic, and machine learning to support accurate risk assessment, monitoring, and smarter lending strategies

A systematic machine learning fairness evaluation framework integrating gender-based data bias quantification and model-level fairness assessment. Tested on 74 disease prediction datasets across 7 machine learning algorithms and 2 fairness metrics, contributing to the development.
Astronomical machine learning framework with advanced data analysis and interactive 3D visualization capabilities.

A novel hybrid machine learning framework combining LSTM and Random Forest models to predict international student academic success with cultural adaptation modeling and early risk detection (Week 8-12).

A graph-based machine learning framework for Aadhaar data analytics focused on regional coverage assessment, location-change anomaly detection, duplicate identity detection, and interactive dashboard visualization for governance and fraud prevention.

BioGraphX is a comprehensive framework for extracting biophysical features from protein sequences using graph-theoretical approaches. The system models proteins as interaction networks where residues form nodes and biochemical interactions form edges, enabling sophisticated feature extraction for downstream machine learning applications
A simple miniature Deep learning framework demonstrating insides of machine learning frameworks
A comprehensive machine learning framework for cryptocurrency price prediction using advanced time series models and financial metrics evaluation.

This repository provides a framework for predicting soil moisture using hydroclimate variables and machine-learning models. It integrates gridded reanalysis data with baseline and physics-informed approaches to evaluate soil-moisture variability, drought persistence, and landsurface predictability over the Colorado River Basin.

An AI-driven adaptive honeypot framework that dynamically deceives attackers, analyzes behavior using machine learning and reinforcement learning, and generates actionable threat intelligence mapped to the MITRE ATT&CK framework.

This repository contains a credit risk model validation framework using machine learning techniques such as XGBoost. The focus is on testing the models performance consistency over different datasets and assessing the stability of the model's features over time through Population Stability Index (PSI).

Machine learning fundamentals implemented from scratch to study optimization, generalization, and model behavior. Built with NumPy to deeply understand gradient descent, backpropagation, and failure modes beyond black-box frameworks.

Designed a two-stage machine learning framework combining Random Forest feature selection and Support Vector Machine (SVM) classification to identify at-risk learners in online education systems.  Achieved improved prediction performance (higher accuracy, recall, and F1-score) compared to baseline models, supporting timely academic intervention.
This master's thesis presents a comprehensive machine learning framework for optimizing LNG regasification process plant in Nigeria.
Quantum Machine Learning for Emotion Detection: A Hybrid QNN Framework
Framework for analysing temporal clinical patterns using clustering and explainable machine learning.
This repository seeks to leverage machine learning frameworks to tackle Valley Fever disease. Goal is to identify compounds that inhibit the disease.
Creating a framework to run Machine Learning and Neural Network

LifePulse is a high-precision machine learning application designed to assist in the early detection of heart disease. Built on a TensorFlow/Keras framework, the core model is a Multi-Layer Artificial Neural Network (ANN) that analyzes 13 critical clinical biomarkers including chest pain type, ST depression, and thallium stress test results.
A machine learning framework to predict loan default risk using alternative borrower data, designed for underserved financial segments.
high-performance machine learning pipeline for regional business data analysis, combining optimized C++ data structures with Python ML frameworks and a Flask web interface

A reproducible framework for auditing domain alignment in latent representations learned from heterogeneous materials datasets. Combines shared-fit PCA/UMAP visualizations, domain separability metrics, and centroid geometry to assess alignment independently of predictive performance.

Health Insurance Cost Prediction App  This web app, which is built with the Streamlit web development framework, uses a machine learning regression algorithm for the purpose of health insurance cost predictions, taking into consideration the personal and lifestyle characteristics of the individual.
An inference server for your machine learning models, including support for multiple frameworks, multi-model serving and more
Collection of machine learning projects spanning healthcare prediction, business analytics, and NLP - built with Python, scikit-learn, and deep learning frameworks.

Predicts customer churn and converts risk scores into actionable retention decisions. The project uses a machine learning model and a cost-benefit framework to select the optimal action threshold based on campaign cost and customer value, enabling targeted interventions and improved retention ROI.
Developed a machine learningbased breast cancer prediction system using Python and optimization techniques like Grid Search and Bayesian Optimization to improve diagnostic accuracy and reliability.
Attempt at Porting LTX-2 Video Model to Apple's MLX Machine Learning Framework
Hyrax - A framework for machine learning in astronomy
